And to the community in general. Many on the windower team, addon authors, the theorycrafters. I hope you enjoy this program as my way to give back.

##Notes

I encourage you to backup your macro files before using this program. I have had no troubles in repeated tests but macros can be troublesome to write.

Because Final Fantasy XI's macro files are protected, this program must be run as administrator.

##Operation

@The files can be opened while in game, but you should shut down before you Save them with this program. This is because FFXI saves the logged-in characters macros from memory as you logout/shutdown.@

@F2@ works like @TAB@ in game and opens an auto-translate menu based on text entered.

You can right click macro buttons, row buttons or the Book selection box to pull up related tasks.

@Revert@ from any of these buttons restores the macro as loaded from the files (File >> Open). Saving files will update the revert cache to the point of saving.

##Shortcuts

@TAB@ or @Enter@ cycles through macro title and macro lines.

@Escape@ takes you to the title line for the macro

@Control + Left@ / @Right@ navigates the control pallette of the macro row.

@Control + 1-9,0@ takes you to the corresponding lefthand  macro in the current row. 0 takes you to the 10th macro of that row.

@Control + Enter@ cycles forward through macros. @Control + Shift + Enter@ Cycles backward.

Likewise for @Alternate@ and the righthand side.

@Control + Up/Down@ navigates rows of the current macro book.

@Alternate + Up/Down@ navigates macro books.

##Tips

One of my favorite things to do, if I'm copying a macro to several rows, is to right-click the macro and copy it and then press @Control+UP/Down@, @Control+V@. Makes it very fast.

